  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Indigenous Communities to Adapt to Climate Change</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam&apos;s Natural Resource Governance and Management Programme (GRENA&apos;s) objective is to reduce inequality and poverty amongst indigenous and rural populations living in the Chaco drylands, to the south, and in the northern Amazon region.  GRENA works to support 12,550 rural and indigenous people, in 30 projects, implemented through 8 local partners. The programme has a budget of &#x20AC; 3.8m over 3 years largely funded by the European Union and the Spanish Cooperation.   To strengthen the capacity of indigenous and rural young people to face the challenges of climate change by managing natural resources, diversifying food production and pushing for environment -friendly public policies.</narrative>
  </description>
